Porcine reproductive and respiratory syndrome, Ecuador
------------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 5 May 2017 from Dr Diego Alfonso Viscaino Cabezas, Ingeniero Agonomo, Ministro de Agricultura, Ganaderia, Acuacultura y Pesca, Ministro de Agricultura, Ganaderia, Acuacultura y Pesca, Quito, Ecuador

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Apr 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Apr 2017
Reason for notification: first occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: Porcine reproductive and respiratory syndrome virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (3128): Km 11 [mi 6.8] v√≠a Quevedo, Luz de America, Santo Domingo, Santo Domingo de los Tsachilas
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Apr 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 469 / 7 / 0 / 7 / 0
Affected population: fattening and trading pigs farms.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 1.49 / 0 / 0 / 1.49
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the event occurred in a commercial farm for breeding and fattening pigs for slaughter; farms with an epidemiological link are being investigated. Surveillance is also being implemented in the outbreak area and in the areas around.

Control measures
Measures applied: screening; disinfection/disinfestation; traceability; quarantine; official destruction of animals products; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal diagnosis Laboratory - Agrocalidad (National laboratory) / Swine / pathogen isolation on cell culture / 26 Apr 2017 / Positive
Animal diagnosis Laboratory - Agrocalidad (National laboratory) / Swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 28 Apr 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

